          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Bremsstrahlung-weighted integrated cross sections for",
                " photoproton and photoneutron emission from  O-17  to",
                " excited  residual  states in N-16 and O-16 have been",
                " measured  by  detecting  the   deexcitation   g-rays",
                " emitted  from  these  states in the residual nuclei.",
                " About  90%  of  photoproton   emission   from   O-17",
                " populates  the  ground  state (2-) and the 0.298 MeV",
                " level  (3-)  in  N-16.  The  remaining   photoproton",
                " emission  lead  to  the 0.120 MeV (0-) and 0.397 MeV",
                " (1-) levels.  For the  O-17(g,n)O-16  reaction,  the",
                " results  show  that emission to bound states in o-16",
                " is predominantly to the 0-16 ground state (0+), with",
                " 4%  of  the  decay  from O-17 giant dipole resonance",
                " going to the 6.13 MeV (3-) excited state; population",
                " of other bound states is not observed."
              ]
            }
          ],
